---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'key-differences', text: 'Key Differences', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'Best Budget Expat Insurance', href: '/best/budget-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Insurance Type', axa: 'Health insurance', safetywing: 'Travel medical' },
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', axa: true, safetywing: 'Limited ($250K max)' },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', axa: true, safetywing: 'Emergency only' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', axa: 'Limited', safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'Maternity', axa: '10-12 mo wait', safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'Pre-existing Conditions', axa: 'Moratorium/underwriting', safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'Routine Care', axa: true, safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'Chronic Conditions', axa: 'Covered', safetywing: 'Not covered' },
  { feature: 'Maximum Coverage', axa: '€3M+', safetywing: '$250K' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'age', header: 'Age' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { age: '30', axa: '$140-220/mo', safetywing: '$45-70/mo' },
  { age: '40', axa: '$190-300/mo', safetywing: '$65-95/mo' },
  { age: '50', axa: '$260-400/mo', safetywing: '$95-140/mo' },
  { age: '60', axa: '$380-580/mo', safetywing: '$150-210/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="AXA Global vs SafetyWing"
  description="Compare AXA Global and SafetyWing insurance. Comprehensive international health insurance vs budget travel medical coverage."
  headline="AXA Global vs SafetyWing"
  subheadline="Established global health insurance vs budget nomad coverage. Understanding what you're buying."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Options"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    AXA Global and SafetyWing represent opposite ends of the international coverage spectrum. AXA is comprehensive health insurance from a global insurance giant; SafetyWing is budget travel medical insurance for nomads. These are fundamentally different products.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">AXA Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Comprehensive health insurance</li>
        <li>One of world's largest insurers</li>
        <li>Covers routine and chronic care</li>
        <li>€3M+ coverage limits</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">SafetyWing</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Travel medical insurance</li>
        <li>Emergency coverage only</li>
        <li>No routine care</li>
        <li>$250K maximum</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Different Products, Different Purposes</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      This comparison isn't about which is "better"—it's about understanding that SafetyWing is travel insurance while AXA is health insurance. They serve different needs at different price points.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    The coverage gap is substantial. AXA covers your ongoing healthcare needs; SafetyWing covers emergencies only.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p><strong>What SafetyWing doesn't cover:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions (completely excluded)</li>
    <li>Routine care, checkups, preventive care</li>
    <li>Mental health treatment</li>
    <li>Maternity (except emergency complications)</li>
    <li>Chronic condition management</li>
    <li>Ongoing prescriptions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    SafetyWing costs 65-70% less than AXA. But you're paying for emergency coverage vs comprehensive health insurance—the price reflects the coverage level.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p><strong>Understanding the price gap:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>At 30: $95-150/mo savings, but no routine care or pre-existing coverage</li>
    <li>At 50: $165-260/mo savings, but one chronic condition could cost thousands</li>
    <li>The coverage maximum alone (€3M+ vs $250K) shows the difference</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="key-differences">Key Differences</h2>

  <h3>Financial Backing</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA:</strong> One of the world's largest insurance companies. Decades of claims-paying history.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Startup founded in 2017. Growing but less established track record.
  </p>

  <h3>Long-term Suitability</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA:</strong> Designed for permanent expats. Lifetime renewal, chronic condition coverage.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Designed for travelers. No lifetime renewal guarantee.
  </p>

  <h3>Coverage Limits</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA:</strong> €3M+ maximum coverage. Adequate for serious illness.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing:</strong> $250K maximum. May be insufficient for major medical events.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose AXA Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're living abroad long-term</li>
        <li>You have or may develop health conditions</li>
        <li>You want routine care covered</li>
        <li>You need mental health coverage</li>
        <li>You want established insurer backing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">SafetyWing May Work If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're young and completely healthy</li>
        <li>You're traveling short-term</li>
        <li>You have zero health conditions</li>
        <li>You accept emergency-only coverage</li>
        <li>Budget is the primary concern</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    For long-term expats or anyone with health considerations, AXA Global is the responsible choice. The comprehensive coverage and established backing justify the higher cost.
  </p>
  <p>
    SafetyWing can work for young, healthy nomads on short adventures who understand the limitations. But it's not a substitute for health insurance—it's emergency travel coverage.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Ask yourself:</strong> If you developed a health condition abroad, would $250K and emergency-only coverage be sufficient? If not, the "savings" from SafetyWing could prove costly.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Comprehensive Coverage"
    description="Compare proper health insurance options."
    buttonText="See All Options"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is travel medical insurance, not comprehensive health insurance. Understand coverage limitations before choosing based on price alone.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
